Class DepthFirstSearch

  • public class DepthFirstSearch
extends java.lang.Object
    The class that is used to hold the data structures and behaviours to carry out the depth first search algorithm on the puzzle to be solved.

      • findPath

        public Path findPath(GridState initialState,
            GridState targetState)
        Carries out the depth first search algorithm on the 8 puzzle to be solved. This method is based on the pseudo code found at: http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Depth-first_search
        Parameters:
        initialState - The initial (starting) state of the puzzle. Represents the tile positions at the start of the puzzle.
        targetState - The target (goal) state that the algorithm is required to try and reach. Represents the tile positions the algorithm is to try and get to by the end of the algorithm.
        Returns:
        The targetState GridState object when the solution is found.
